President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Julie Brill, a resident of North Carolina and Vermont, was nominated for Commissioner of the Federal Trade Commission. Edith Ramirez, a partner in a law firm in Los Angeles, was nominated for Commissioner of the Federal Trade Commission. Scott H. DeLisi, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, was nominated for Ambassador to the Federal Democratic Republic of Nepal. Beatrice W. Welters, President and Chairman of the AnBryce Foundation, was nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago. Earl F. Gohl Jr., who has 20 years of experience in Pennsylvania state and local government, was nominated for Federal Co-Chair of the Appalachian Regional Commission.